article.headline: Youngstown State destroys Westminster 108-57
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- Bobby Hain scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds as Youngstown State easily defeated Division III Westminster 108-57 on Saturday. Youngstown State (6-1) had five players score in double figures, including Marcus Keene with 15 and 13 from Kendrick Perry. The Penguins had a school record 66 rebounds and had 10 blocked shots -- all in the first half. The 10 rejections were four away from a single-game school record. The Penguins made 27 of 31 free throws, while Westminster only attempted eight. Youngstown State made 45.9 percent of its shots, including 13 of 33 from behind the arc. Paul Carswell had a game-high 21 points and was the only Titan player to score more than seven points. Westminster grabbed 46 fewer rebounds than Youngstown State and made just 30.8 percent of its shots.
